RA_-_7717866.jpg","cap":"Crowley's Ridge Parkway Delta Cultural Center","desc":"The Delta Cultural Center, shown here, was established to preserve the legacy of the land and the people of the Mississippi Delta, through education and entertainment. Location: Arkansas (34.539° N 90.545° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Dennis Adams","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Crowley%27s_Ridge_Parkway_-_Delta_Cultural_Center_-_NARA_-_7717866.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Crowley%27s_Ridge_Parkway_-_Delta_Cultural_Center_Exhibit_-_NARA_-_7717879.jpg/1280px-Crowley%27s_Ridge_Parkway_-_Delta_Cultural_Center_Exhibit_-_NARA_-_7717879.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/8d/Crowley%27s_Ridge_Parkway_-_Delta_Cultural_Center_Exhibit_-_NARA_-_7717879.jpg","cap":"Crowley's Ridge Parkway Delta Cultural Center Exhibit","desc":"The blues music tradition of the Arkansas Delta is one of the many stories told at the Delta Cultural Center in Helena, a primary interpretive center along The Great River Road. Exhibits also tell a comprehensive story of the land and its people from prehistoric times to the present. Location: Arkansas (34.522° N 90.586° W) Status: Public domain. Arkansas Delta Byways: Cranford Johnson Robinson Wo","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Crowley%27s_Ridge_Parkway_-_Delta_Cultural_Center_Exhibit_-_NARA_-_7717879.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/76/Crowley%27s_Ridge_Parkway_-_Evening_Lake_-_NARA_-_7717869.jpg/1280px-Crowley%27s_Ridge_Parkway_-_Evening_Lake_-_NARA_-_7717869.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/76/Crowley%27s_Ridge_Parkway_-_Evening_Lake_-_NARA_-_7717869.jpg","cap":"Crowley's Ridge Parkway Evening Lake","desc":"Trees reflect in the gently rippling waters of Evening Lake. Location: Crowley's Ridge Parkway, Arkansas (36.047° N 90.667° W) Status: Public domain.","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Crowley%27s_Ridge_Parkway_-_Evening_Lake_-_NARA_-_7717869.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/92/Crowley%27s_Ridge_Parkway_-_Hemingway-Pfeiffer_Museum_and_Conference_Center_-_NARA_-_7717871.jpg/1280px-Crowley%27s_Ridge_Parkway_-_Hemingway-Pfeiffer_Museum_and_Conference_Center_-_NARA_-_7717871.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/92/Crowley%27s_Ridge_Parkway_-_Hemingway-Pfeiffer_Museum_and_Conference_Center_-_NARA_-_7717871.jpg","cap":"Crowley's Ridge Parkway Hemingway Pfeiffer Museum and Conference Cente","desc":"Hemingway wrote portions of his novel, , at this home in Piggott, Arkansas, now a visitor center of the Crowley's Ridge Parkway. Location: Piggott, Arkansas (36.380° N 90.183° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Dennis Adams","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Crowley%27s_Ridge_Parkway_-_Hemingway-Pfeiffer_Museum_and_Conference_Center_-_NARA_-_7717871.jpg"}],"counts":{}}